author: COMSOL
description: Including circumferential displacements in a 2D axisymmetric Solid Mechanics interface allows twist and bending deformations to be computed. This model determines stress concentration factors for a hollow shaft for load cases of axial extension, torsion as well as bending using a computationally lean 2D axisymmetric formulation. To demonstrate their equivalence, the model setup and results are compared with a full 3D analysis.
